snippet.textDisplay:
You do realise you could have done this with an ethernet or WiFi enabled Arduino and simply port the code over to C/C++ right? For something as simple as this, an Arduino is a much more efficient device than a RasPi. In an era in which we are meant to be reducing energy usage, your wasting energy by using a computer to do something that can be done with a low power microcontroller.
14 hours to solder like 30 SMD LEDs....wow. You should also not drive those LEDs directly from the RasPi 3.3V pin, that is such bad practice. The 3.3V pin should never exceed 50mA or you will damage the CPU or voltage regulator.
snippet.textOriginal:
You do realise you could have done this with an ethernet or WiFi enabled Arduino and simply port the code over to C/C++ right? In an era in which we are meant to be reducing energy usage, your wasting energy by using a computer to do something that can be done with a low power microcontroller.
